kernel-5.15-rt-xanmod1 x86_64
Only run build-all-kernel-pkgs.sh

This kernel unlock some serious performance improvements
install this before wine-tkg

"Huge page tables" is a nice performance boost, but can be a minor security risk.
I might change something about the configuration but this has been working good for me for a long time.
You are free to swap the configuration before you build, just avoid changing the file name.
This configuration is not too far from generic Slackware.

https://xanmod.org/

Run first time to avoid conflicts with pkgs:
removepkg kernel-source kernel-generic kernel-modules kernel-headers

To install:
upgradepkg --install-new --reinstall /tmp/output-x86_64-5.15.44-rt46-xanmod1/kernel*.txz

Initrd command:
/usr/share/mkinitrd/mkinitrd_command_generator.sh -k 5.15.44-rt46-xanmod1

You can swap out the configuration file but don't add localversion, it have not been tested with the script.
the configuration must be the same version name AND you must have run make oldconfig for the version you are compiling.
If you want to upgrade the kernel yourself, the script is really nice for this,
just build with the ???-xanmod1.tar.gz you want and put it next to build-all-kernel-pkgs.sh and go.

You might want to blacklist: /etc/slackpkg/blacklist

kernel-source
kernel-headers

Disclaimer you can use kernel-modules without a pkg conflict.
But remember you should have the appropriate kernel-headers installed when compiling software drivers or wine that target specific kernel functionality

Don't forget you're mkinitrd command and lilo/elilo or whatever bootloader you're using!
It happens like once a year when we had too much to drink right?
I always keep the huge kernel pkg for this...

Note: The current proprietary NVIDIA, VirtualBox, VMware Workstation / Player and some other dkms modules builds do not officially support THIS RT kernel

For building VirtualBox:
Just build from sbopkg and use link normal on you're other kernel
If you get errors like: failed to execute '/usr/share/virtualbox/VBoxCreateUSBNode.sh' '/usr/share/virtualbox/VBoxCreateUSBNode.sh 189 0 09 vboxusers': No such file or directory
You probably have this udev configuration in initrd when it loads usb drivers on you dont need to worry about it.
if it feels too dirty you could move and /lib/udev/rules.d/.10-virtualbox.rules run:/etc/rc.d/rc.udev reload
and move back the file.

        # Avoid virtualbox startup service early for xanmod1
        if echo $(uname -a) | grep xanmod1 > /dev/null; then
          chmod -x /etc/rc.d/rc.vbox*
        else
          chmod +x /etc/rc.d/rc.vbox*
        fi

blacklist virtualbox-kernel because if you are using another kernel it want to upgrade the modules on the existing one..
to keep it clean, remember you must rebuild when there is a kernel update manually!

and before you run virtualbox: sudo modprobe vboxdrv

For building NVIDIA:
IGNORE_PREEMPT_RT_PRESENCE=1

Don't do this, just use nouveau, if you have nvidia don't game with this kernel, maybe it works for you anyway..
BTW gaming is nice with this kernel :)
